Day 10: Excel Text Functions
Today, I learned and practiced important Excel Text Functions used for data cleaning and text manipulation.
Functions Covered
CONCAT
CONCATENATE
TEXTJOIN
LEFT
RIGHT
MID
SUBSTITUTE
LEN
UPPER
LOWER
PROPER
Key Takeaways
Combined text from multiple cells.
Extracted specific characters from text strings.
Replaced text values efficiently.
Counted characters in text entries.
Standardized text formatting using uppercase, lowercase, and proper case functions.
Why It Matters
Text functions are essential for cleaning and preparing raw data before analysis. They help transform inconsistent data into a structured format suitable for reporting and decision-making.
